    <h4>
        Welcome to the Tourney Bracket Control 2.1 QuickStart Tutorial</h4>
    The QuickStart Tutorial is designed to help you learn how to use all of the advanced
    features of the Tourney Bracket Control quickly. <a href="http://www.tourneylogic.com/products/bracketcontrol/bracketDownloads.aspx">
        Download the source code of this QuickStart</a> to learn how easy it is to build
    your own applications with the Tourney Bracket Control.<br />
    <br />
    <strong>Release Notes:</strong>
    <br />
    <ul>
        <li>Tourney Bracket Control 2.1 was built with Microsoft .Net Framework 2.0. It is not
            backwards compatible with Tourney Bracket Control 1.0 or .Net 1.1.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        <strong>Install Insturctions:</strong></p>
    <ol>
        <li>Unzip the QuickStart files into a location on your machine or server.</li>
        <li>Set a virtual directory to point at the root folder location you unzipped to.&nbsp;
        </li>
        <li>Make sure the virtual directory is set to ASP.NET 2.0 or above.</li>
        <li>Change the App_Data directory to have modify access for the Network Service (Win
            2003 or &gt;) or ASPNET (XP or &lt;) user.</li>
    </ol>
